Author: smk762#7640
Content:
Generally the ICT (and other skills) experience of candidates is demonstrated via previous activity within the community. Last year, a number of candidates that were highly active in LABS (which has its own NNs for testing new things) won a spot after showing capability. 
There is also a testnet for candidates to participate in prior to elections, which offers a chance to figure things out and show what you can do, both in terms of actual notarisation and with writing code (and sharing it) to help all NNs improve node management etc - https://notarystats.info/testnet.php
